# Moduvox Project Rules — Synced with CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md

## AI Collaboration
This file is kept in sync with CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, .windsurfrules, and GEMINI.md.

## Stack
- Next.js App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, Radix UI, shadcn/ui, Recharts
- Supabase (Auth + Database only — no Supabase Storage), AES-256 encryption for API keys
- Hosting: Vercel (frontend), Railway (worker)
- Integrations: Resend (email), Dodo Payments, Google Gemini AI, Gradio/HuggingFace VoxCPM
- Cloudflare R2 for all file storage

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript strict — no `any`
- Server Components by default — `"use client"` only when needed
- Response envelope: `{ data: T }` on success, `{ error: string }` on error
- kebab-case routes, PascalCase types, camelCase variables, snake_case DB columns
- Mobile-first: touch targets 48x48px+, base font 16px+
- All API routes use Zod validation
- All list endpoints paginated
- RLS enabled on every Supabase table

## Vercel Middleware
CRITICAL: Always add a `config.matcher` to `middleware.ts`. Never ship without one.

## Git Conventions
- `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/` branch prefixes
- Present-tense imperative commits: "add Slack alert channel"
- Commit after each fix or feature — don't batch unrelated changes
- Never commit `.env*`, `node_modules`, `.next/`, `graphify-out/`

## AI Patterns to Follow
- Always load relevant skills before tasks
- Check LESSONS.md at the start of every session
- Surface tradeoffs, state assumptions, push back when warranted
- Simplicity first — minimum code, no speculative features
- Surgical changes — touch only what's needed
- Goal-driven — define success criteria before implementing
